  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Learning deep latent variable models ",
    "bbox": [
      27,
      197,
      171,
      213
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Latentvariablemodels ",
    "bbox": [
      27,
      229,
      117,
      243
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\np (\\mathbf {x}; \\boldsymbol {\\theta}) = \\int p (\\mathbf {x} \\mid z; \\boldsymbol {\\theta}) p (z) d z\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      110,
      244,
      220,
      281
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Gradient overmodel parameters ",
    "bbox": [
      27,
      285,
      153,
      299
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\nabla_ {\\boldsymbol {\\theta}} \\mathbb {E} _ {\\hat {p} _ {\\mathrm {d a t a} (\\mathbf {x})}} [ \\log p (\\boldsymbol {x}; \\boldsymbol {\\theta}) ] \\approx \\frac {1}{n} \\sum_ {i = 1} ^ {n} \\mathbb {E} _ {p \\left(\\boldsymbol {z} ^ {(i)} \\mid \\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(i)}; \\boldsymbol {\\theta}\\right)} \\left[ \\nabla_ {\\boldsymbol {\\theta}} \\log p \\left(\\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(i)}, \\boldsymbol {z} ^ {(i)}; \\boldsymbol {\\theta}\\right) \\right]\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      38,
      300,
      294,
      344
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "sub_type": "text",
    "list_items": [
      "·To learna latent variablemodel via gradientascent,we need to approximate the expectationover the latentposterior $p ( \\mathbf { z } \\mid \\mathbf { x } ; \\mathbf { \\boldsymbol { \\theta } } )$ which is intractableingeneral. ",
      "·Variational inference isadominantapproach ofapproximation (e.g.,VAE [1]),but theapproximationpower is limited. ",
      "Markovchain MonteCarlo(MCMC)iscapableof approximatecomplex posteriors,but istoo slowdue todatapoint-wise iterations. "
    ],
    "bbox": [
      28,
      355,
      299,
      478
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Preliminary ",
    "text_level": 1,
    "bbox": [
      27,
      491,
      94,
      512
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Langevindynamics ",
    "bbox": [
      27,
      521,
      104,
      537
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "·Langevindynamics[2]isa gradient-based MCMC. ",
    "bbox": [
      28,
      555,
      216,
      572
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\begin{array}{l} z ^ {\\prime} \\sim q (z ^ {\\prime} \\mid z) = \\mathcal {N} (z ^ {\\prime}; z + \\eta \\nabla_ {z} \\log p (x, z; \\theta), 2 \\eta I) \\\\ z \\leftarrow z ^ {\\prime} \\text {w i t h p r o b a b i l i t y} \\min  \\left\\{1, \\frac {p (x , z ^ {\\prime} ; \\theta) q (z \\mid z ^ {\\prime})}{p (x , z ; \\theta) q (z ^ {\\prime} \\mid z)} \\right\\} \\\\ \\end{array}\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      60,
      589,
      269,
      663
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "sub_type": "text",
    "list_items": [
      "·Byrepeating thisiterative update,thesamplesasymptoticallyapproach to thetrue posterior $p ( \\mathbf { z } \\mid \\mathbf { x } ; \\pmb \\theta )$ ",
      "·MCMC iterationsare independentlyperformed foreach posterior per datapoint $p ( z ^ { ( i ) } \\mid \\boldsymbol { x } ^ { ( i ) } ; \\boldsymbol { \\theta } )$ for $i = 1 , . . . , n$ "
    ],
    "bbox": [
      28,
      670,
      297,
      745
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "→How can we amortize the cost of datapoint-wise iterations? ",
    "bbox": [
      27,
      764,
      263,
      779
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "image",
    "img_path": "output/Langevin Autoencoders for Learning Deep Latent Variable Models_poster/visuals/images/fig_1.jpg",
    "image_caption": [],
