    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Method ",
    "text_level": 1,
    "bbox": [
      359,
      165,
      406,
      185
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Amortized Langevin dynamics ",
    "bbox": [
      359,
      197,
      477,
      213
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "image",
    "img_path": "output/Langevin Autoencoders for Learning Deep Latent Variable Models_poster/visuals/images/fig_3.jpg",
    "image_caption": [],
    "image_footnote": [],
    "bbox": [
      359,
      233,
      518,
      388
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "image",
    "img_path": "output/Langevin Autoencoders for Learning Deep Latent Variable Models_poster/visuals/images/fig_4.jpg",
    "image_caption": [],
    "image_footnote": [],
    "bbox": [
      526,
      278,
      590,
      344
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "sub_type": "text",
    "list_items": [
      "·Inouramortized Langevin dynamics (ALD),we prepareanencoder that mapsthe observeddata into the latent variable,andrun MCMCon its parameterspace. ",
      "·Markovchain onthe latent space is implicitlyperformed by collectingthe output of the encoder. ",
      "·Our main theorem shows that theALDis validas MCMC if the encoder takes the form of: "
    ],
    "bbox": [
      359,
      411,
      636,
      530
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\nf _ {\\mathbf {z} | \\mathbf {x}} (x; \\boldsymbol {\\Phi}) = \\Phi g (x).\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      459,
      534,
      536,
      553
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "·Itcan beeasily implemented usinganeural netwhose parametersare fixed exceptforthelastlinearlayer. ",
    "bbox": [
      359,
      556,
      632,
      589
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Langevin Autoencoder ",
    "bbox": [
      359,
      597,
      447,
      612
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "sub_type": "text",
    "list_items": [
      "·ALDcan be applied to the training of deep latent variable models (DLVMs) byslightlymodifying the learningalgorithmof traditional autoencoders. ",
      "·Wecallthis learning algorithm of DLVMs the Langevinautoencoder (LAE). "
    ],
    "bbox": [
      359,
      621,
      635,
      672
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "$\\theta , \\Phi , \\psi $ Initialize parameters ",
    "bbox": [
      376,
      688,
      500,
      704
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "repeat ",
    "bbox": [
      377,
      707,
      407,
      718
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\begin{array}{l} \\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(1)}, \\dots , \\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(n)} \\sim \\hat {p} (\\mathbf {x}) \\\\ \\mathbf {f o r} t = 0, \\dots , T - 1 \\mathbf {d o} \\\\ V _ {t} = - \\sum_ {i = 1} ^ {n} \\log p (\\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(i)}, \\boldsymbol {z} ^ {(i)} = \\boldsymbol {\\Phi} g (\\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(i)}; \\boldsymbol {\\psi}); \\boldsymbol {\\theta}) \\\\ \\boldsymbol {\\Phi} ^ {\\prime} \\sim q (\\boldsymbol {\\Phi} ^ {\\prime} \\mid \\boldsymbol {\\Phi}) := \\mathcal {N} (\\boldsymbol {\\Phi} ^ {\\prime}; \\boldsymbol {\\Phi} - \\eta \\nabla_ {\\boldsymbol {\\Phi}} V _ {t}, 2 \\eta \\boldsymbol {I}) \\\\ V _ {t} ^ {\\prime} = - \\sum_ {i = 1} ^ {n} \\log p (\\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(i)}, \\boldsymbol {z} ^ {(i)} = \\boldsymbol {\\Phi} ^ {\\prime} g (\\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(i)}; \\boldsymbol {\\psi}); \\boldsymbol {\\theta}) \\\\ \\Phi \\leftarrow \\Phi^ {\\prime} \\text {w i t h p r o b a b i l i t y m i n} \\left\\{1, \\frac {\\exp (- V (\\phi^ {\\prime})) q (\\phi | \\phi^ {\\prime})}{\\exp (- V (\\phi)) q (\\phi^ {\\prime} | \\phi)} \\right\\} \\\\ \\end{array}\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      391,
      719,
      609,
      833
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "end for ",
    "bbox": [
      391,
      833,
      423,
      845
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\nV _ {T} = - \\sum_ {i = 1} ^ {n} \\log p (\\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(i)}, \\boldsymbol {z} ^ {(i)} = \\Phi g (\\boldsymbol {x} ^ {(i)}; \\psi); \\boldsymbol {\\theta})\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      391,
      845,
      572,
      864
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\boldsymbol {\\theta} \\leftarrow \\boldsymbol {\\theta} - \\eta \\nabla_ {\\boldsymbol {\\theta}} \\frac {1}{T} \\sum_ {t = 1} ^ {T} V _ {t}\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      391,
      864,
      483,
      884
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\boldsymbol {\\psi} \\leftarrow \\boldsymbol {\\psi} - \\eta \\nabla_ {\\boldsymbol {\\psi}} \\frac {1}{T} \\sum_ {t = 1} ^ {T} V _ {t}\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      391,
      884,
      488,
      902
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "until convergence of parameters ",
    "bbox": [
      377,
      902,
      504,
      917
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "return $\\theta , \\Phi , \\psi$ ",
    "bbox": [
      377,
      917,
      438,
      932
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
